Package com.spiderweb

Class SpiderWebNode<E>

java.lang.Object
com.spiderweb.SpiderWebNode<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements stored in the SpiderWebNode
public class SpiderWebNode<E> extends Object
The SpiderWebNode class represents a node in the SpiderWeb data structure, where each node stores a value and maintains references to its next and previous nodes, as well as references to nodes on the next and previous levels.

Example Usage: 

 SpiderWebNode<Integer> node = new SpiderWebNode<>(42, null, null);
Since:
November 21, 2023
